      • initDefaultCommand

        public void initDefaultCommand()
        Description copied from class: edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem
        Initialize the default command for a subsystem By default subsystems have no default command, but if they do, the default command is set with this method. It is called on all Subsystems by CommandBase in the users program after all the Subsystems are created.
        Specified by:
        initDefaultCommand in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.Subsystem

      • returnPIDInput

        protected double returnPIDInput()
        This function sends the grabber angle to the PID controller. In order to calculate the grabber angle, it has to take in the voltage from the magnetic encoder, convert it to an angle, and then send it to the PID controller.
        Specified by:
        returnPIDInput in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.PIDSubsystem
        Returns:
        Grabber angle

      • usePIDOutput

        protected void usePIDOutput(double output)
        Description copied from class: edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.PIDSubsystem
        Uses the value that the pid loop calculated. The calculated value is the "output" parameter. This method is a good time to set motor values, maybe something along the lines of driveline.tankDrive(output, -output)

        All subclasses of PIDSubsystem must override this method.

        Specified by:
        usePIDOutput in class edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.command.PIDSubsystem
        Parameters:
        output - the value the pid loop calculated

      • atSetpoint

        public boolean atSetpoint()
        This function tells us if we're at the setpoint (useful for knowing if a command has finished). It returns true if we're within an inch of the setpoint.
        Returns:
        atSetpoint? (True if less than 1 inch from setpoint)
